<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-04T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-04T16:36:00-05:00" n="1134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1134">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/251</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-04T15:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1916, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>545. To-day’s press publishes statement of Fomento Department as follows:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>All permits, laws, decrees, leases, on oil lands issued, granted
                                    or authorized, by State Governments for the exploration,
                                    exploitation and trading of minerals, <pb facs="0852" n="776" xml:id="pg_776"/> coals, bitumenoil and all other
                                    hydrocarbons of hydrogen, regardless of its state, are declared
                                    null and void and are of the competence of the general Federal
                                    Government. This applies presumably to all acts issued since the
                                    establishment of the de facto Government.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>